        "description": "Typical for pulsed 1064 nm lasers in cleaning; 30 kHz recommended for plaster to achieve fast coverage without excessive heat buildup, trading off speed vs. thermal load. Higher rates (>50 kHz) risk accumulation on low-conductivity substrates. Source: Academic literature, e.g., Appl. Surf. Sci. (2019) on stone/plaster cleaning parameters."
