        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 1000,
        "value": 20,
        "unit": "ns",
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred for cost-effective cleaning of plaster; picosecond (ps) or femtosecond reduces HAZ but less common at 1064 nm for industrial use. 20 ns minimizes heat accumulation on low-melting-point plaster (~150°C dehydration). Source: Laser physics research in Opt. Lasers Eng. (2015) on ablation of calcium sulfate materials."
      },
